race.comment: MAGNOLIA SKY (6) just missed here on debut and then came back and belted the Maidens by 4L from the front. Drawn to go forward again and keeps Burke's handy 3kg claim. Fitter again and she looks capable of taking the next step. NOVALARGO (7) brings a comfortable Launceston Maiden win to resumption and won a recent Longford trial by a space. Jumps from an inside barrier and may control the race. Will be naturally improved and has to be considered. ZAMBEZI BLONDE (3) resumes off a Maiden win here and keeps the in-form Byrne Burke. Has upside and keep safe as well. ROUNDLE PARK (5) peaks and disappointed when backed off the map at Launceston a month ago. He may be worth another chance.
